<subSubSection id="44911484C516BD57FF45FEE65243FE64" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0C34470FC516BD57FF45FEE65243FE64" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC516BD57FF45FEE6502FFED1" bold="true" box="[199,327,330,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Comment:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC516BD57FECFFEE7508AFED1" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[333,482,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC516BD57FECFFEE7508AFED1" box="[333,482,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Centris varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly variable in the coloration of the integument and the pubescence. Both sexes have dichromatic forms with intermediary forms between them. In addition, in this species there are metander males which are totally different in size, coloration and pubescence. All these variations are reflected in the large number of junior synonyms of this species (see 
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC516BD57FDD0FE1B5277FE64" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[594,799,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC516BD57FD21FE1B53BDFE64" box="[675,725,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
